==Evolutionary psychiatry / Clinical evolutionary psychology==

As noted in the table below, adaptationist hypotheses regarding the etiology of psychological disorders are often based on analogies with evolutionary perspectives on medicine and physiological dysfunctions (see in particular, [[Randolph M. Nesse|Randy Nesse]] and [[George C. Williams]]' book ''[http://www.amazon.com/Why-We-Get-Sick-Darwinian/dp/0679746749/ Why We Get Sick]'').<ref>Nesse, R., & Williams, G. (1996) Why We Get Sick. NY: Vintage.</ref>
[[Evolutionary_medicine#Evolutionary_psychiatry|Evolutionary psychiatrists]] and psychologists suggest that some mental disorders likely have multiple causes.<ref name="Gaulin, Steven J. C 2003. p 1-24">Gaulin, Steven J. C. and Donald H. McBurney. Evolutionary psychology. Prentice Hall. 2003. ISBN 978-0-13-111529-3, Chapter 1, p 1-24.</ref>

